question: Gán-tsúi ê tāi-piáu ūi-tī in 'Tē-it soán-tiō' nî-tsūn sí-tsūn tn̂g-tsú-liâu, hōo-tsò in tshián-tshián-á ūi-tiâu-khui ê lúi?
Koa-tōa ê tāi-piáu ê siông-sò͘, sī in siūⁿ tē 1 pái soán-tiō tiō sī 2002 nî ê ūi-tiám, sī siáⁿ-choáⁿ ê sò͘-liōng?
Tui-túi chiah-ê tāi-piáu ūi-tāi sióⁿ-chiáⁿ nî tòe-ê chham-chèng-jîn, i sī hō͘ lán kiàⁿ chòe siáⁿ-chiáⁿ tóng? (Which political party is represented by the delegate with the earliest election year?)
Chhiūⁿ liat chē-chē chham-ka chha-chí 'Appropriations' he̍k-chiá 'Environmental Matters' úi-oân-hoē ê Democratic tāi-piáu ê miâ?
answer: Weir, Michael H. Jr. Michael H. Weir, Jr.
Jones, Adrienne A. Adrienne A. Jones
DeBoy, Steven J. Sr. Steven J. DeBoy, Sr.
Lafferty, Stephen W. Stephen W. Lafferty

question: Tī chit ê piáu lāi ê tāi-piáu lāi, ū chek-hūn ê oáⁿ-tó͘ sī tūa-bîn-chú tóng ê?

Rua-ti rule chuah, jimi-khi delegate coi-eng chiap-o-liau chiap-o-liau koan-hām chhīⁿ-chhīⁿ ê, chiah-beh iōng 'Appropriations'committee, hūi-chúi delegate su-ài kā iōng-choân committee tiāⁿ-tiāⁿ lâi kái?
answer: Impallaria, Richard K. Richard K. Impallaria
Jennings, J. B. J. B. Jennings
McDonough, Patrick L. Patrick L. McDonough
Malone, James E. Jr. James E. Malone, Jr.

question: In pai-liau list la-i, koan-î chiah ū siok chē ê delegate ê lūn-uî?
Ngoaⁿ cheng-cheng 1990 ni nî chìn-chá chhut-jīm ê tāi-piáu, kah 2002 ni nî chhut-jīm ê tāi-piáu píⁿ-kàu, siáⁿ chi̍t phài ū khah chē Republican?
answer: 2002 ni nî chhut-jīm ê chi̍t phài ū khah chē Republican. Chiah-ê tī 1990 ni nî chìn-chá chhut-jīm ê saⁿ ūi tāi-piáu (Kach, Minnick, McDonough) tiong, nn̄g ū Republican (66.7%). Chiah-ê tī 2002 ni nî chhut-jīm ê kiú ūi tāi-piáu tiong, gō͘ ū Republican (55.6%). Só͘-í, 1990 ni nî chìn-chá ê chi̍t phài ū khah chē Republican.

question: Án-chúin ê chu-liāu ū tián-sī sán-seng liân-koaⁿ, chi̍t ê khu tāi-piáu chē-ê koān (county) kap in tāi-piáu ê chèng-tóng chha-piat ê koan-hē b?
answer: Ū, liāu-lō͘ thè chhut ū khó-lêng ê koan-hē.Ū saⁿ ê khu tāi-piáu chē-ê koān: 05.2 5B, 07.0 7, kap 12.1 12A. Tī chia ê khu lāi, chhóng-kiōng ū la̍k ūi tāi-piáu, lîm-tiong ū sì ūi sī Republican, nn̄g ūi sī Democratic. Tùi pí, chha-piat sī tāi-piáu chi̍t ê koān (Baltimore County) ê khu, si̍p-saⁿ ūi tāi-piáu lāi, cha̍p ūi sī Democratic. Chiah ē kóaⁿ-chhut, tī chiah ê chu-liāu lāi, sióⁿ-kē koān ê khu koh-khah ū khó-lêng hō͘ Republican tāi-piáu.

question: Chhap chhit (1974) kàu chhit-la̍k (2006) chi kan, chha-khuì sin soán chhut ê tāi-piáu tī chong-phài (party) téng-bīn ê kái-piàn chóaⁿ-iūⁿ? Ū liáu-kái ê chu-sè bē?
answer: Tī "Tē-it chò soán" ê nî-tāi lâi kóng, bô khah bêng-chhián, pêng-chhun ê chu-sè, pí-lâi sī ū piàn-tōng. Tī chhit-cha̍p nî-tāi kah pa̍t-cha̍p nî-tāi, tāi-piáu sī lán chhiúⁿ (2 Republican, 1 Democrat). Chhit-cha̍p nî-tāi ê sî-chūn, chhut-hiān chē koánkiat ê Democratic lâi, 5 ê sin soán chhut ê tāi-piáu lāi-bīn, 4 ê sī Democratic. Siōng chē ê chi̍t ê khò, chiū sī 2002 nî, sī khah tōa ê Republican chiah ū 5 ê Republican kah 4 ê Democratic. Chòe-āu chi̍t ê nî, 2006 nî, kan-na Democrat chiū-sī soán chhut. Chiòng-chóng lâi kóng, ê chu-sè bô sī chi̍t-tiâu-á; i óaⁿ liáu chi̍t-tiâu chi̍t-tiâu ê Democratic, chi̍t-tiâu chi̍t-tiâu ê kiat-hêng, koh tòe lē Democratic.
